America, with its isles, embraces at present (1830) twelve independent states,
                    and various colonies belonging to six European powers. The states are, 1.
                    Brazil; 2. Co-ombia; 3. Peru; 4. Bolivia or Upper Peru; 5. La Plata; 3. Chili;
                    7. Paraguay; 8. Banda Oriental; 9. Guatema-a; 10. Mexico 11. the United States;
                    12. Hayti. The colonies belong to Russia, Britain, Denmark, the Netherlands,
                    France, and Spain.
